com.example.mdbook

Class User

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.example.mdbook.User

  • public abstract class User
extends java.lang.Object
    Holds contact information relevant to a user. Has no verification or online sync methods. Class (and subclasses) should never be interacted with directly by the user or activities. The UserManager, UserController and ElasticSearchController classes are tasked with verifying, authenticating, saving and loading user data. The User, Patient and Caregiver classes are simply there to help with organizing and passing data. Acts as superclass to Patient and Caregiver
    See Also:
    Patient, Caregiver, UserController, UserManager
